---
title: Astro
name: Astro
description: Send email from an Astro API route with the top-level mail().
category: Frameworks
---

Postboi is framework-agnostic â€” read the request's `FormData` in an API route and hand it
straight to [`mail()`](/api). Postboi extracts the [special fields](/formdata#special-fields)
and renders the rest into a tidy HTML table.

```typescript
// src/pages/api/contact.ts
import type { APIRoute } from 'astro';
import { mail } from 'postboi';

export const POST: APIRoute = async ({ request, redirect }) => {
	const form = await request.formData();

	// Reply-to comes from the submitted email, so replying reaches the sender.
	form.set('_reply_to', String(form.get('contactâ†’email') ?? ''));
	form.set('_subject', 'Contact Form');

	await mail({ body: form });
	return redirect('/?sent=1', 303);
};
```

Point a `multipart/form-data` form at the route with fields like `contactâ†’name`,
`contactâ†’email`, and `detailsâ†’message` â€” the [`fieldsetâ†’field`](/formdata#grouped-fields)
syntax groups them in the email. API routes need SSR, so set `output: 'server'` with an
adapter in `astro.config.mjs`.

The provider and default recipient come from [`postboi.config.ts`](/config) â€” a
`POSTBOI_TOKEN` routes to [Postboi Cloud](/cloud), or pick any [provider](/providers).

**Runnable example:** [`examples/astro-provider-postboi`](https://github.com/darbymanning/postboi/tree/main/examples/astro-provider-postboi).
